Li Bai  is widely regarded as the greatest poet of the Tang Dynasty and a towering figure in Chinese literature. Known as the "Immortal Poet," he composed over a thousand poems celebrated for their vivid imagery, romantic spirit, and profound love for nature and wine. His verses often depict moonlit nights, flowing rivers, and towering mountains, reflecting his free-spirited, unrestrained personality. Li Bai's work embodies the essence of Tang poetry—bold, imaginative, and emotionally powerful. His influence extends far beyond China, inspiring readers worldwide with his celebration of life, friendship, and the beauty of the natural world.

